01:31.807 --> 01:33.247
Is that them?

01:36.287 --> 01:37.814
Jesus Christ.

01:37.887 --> 01:40.255
Are they going to do it right here?

01:45.847 --> 01:47.767
You guys ever been through this before?

01:48.367 --> 01:49.446
No.

01:50.247 --> 01:53.766
It's best to ignore it, keep your
head down, and go back to work.

01:53.767 --> 01:54.814
Go on.

02:01.367 --> 02:02.775
Don't watch.

02:21.607 --> 02:23.047
Timothy Singh?

02:23.606 --> 02:26.171
- Yes.
- I'm afraid we have to speak with you.

02:26.246 --> 02:27.294
Come.

02:41.846 --> 02:43.166
Eric Dale?

02:43.846 --> 02:44.966
Excuse me?

02:44.967 --> 02:46.134
Eric Dale?

02:47.406 --> 02:48.770
- No.
- Sorry?

02:49.367 --> 02:50.567
I'm not Eric Dale.

02:50.846 --> 02:52.691
I'm so sorry.

02:52.766 --> 02:53.846
He's my boss.

02:54.446 --> 02:56.093
He's down the hall.

02:56.166 --> 02:57.290
Thanks.

03:11.646 --> 03:13.926
Excuse me, Mr. Dale?

03:14.885 --> 03:16.129
This way.

03:24.526 --> 03:25.769
Okay.

04:03.845 --> 04:06.813
I am obviously sorry
that we are here today.

04:06.885 --> 04:11.130
But these are extraordinary times,
as you very well must know.

04:11.845 --> 04:14.124
Look, I run Risk Management.

04:14.125 --> 04:17.324
I don't really see how that's a
natural place to start cutting jobs.

04:17.325 --> 04:19.692
We hope you understand
this is in no way personal.

04:19.694 --> 04:22.729
The majority of this floor
is being let go today.

04:25.165 --> 04:28.689
Ms. Bratberg is now going to run through
the details of what the firm is offering.

04:30.365 --> 04:31.609
Okay.

04:31.684 --> 04:36.006
Mr. Dale, the firm is offering you
a six-month severance at half your salary.

04:36.325 --> 04:39.844
You will keep all unvested options
that you currently hold.

04:39.845 --> 04:41.765
Health will be extended
through that period.

04:41.844 --> 04:47.485
You have until tomorrow at 4:47 to either
take the offer or it will be revoked.

04:48.004 --> 04:49.171
Do you understand?

04:50.685 --> 04:51.732
Yes.

04:52.404 --> 04:53.923
Unfortunately, Mr. Dale,

04:53.924 --> 04:56.412
due to the highly sensitive nature
of your work here,

04:56.485 --> 04:59.843
the firm has to take certain precautions
for security purposes

04:59.844 --> 05:03.403
that may seem punitive in nature.

05:03.404 --> 05:05.324
I hope, considering your

05:07.204 --> 05:09.644
over 19 years of service to the firm,

05:09.645 --> 05:12.843
you will understand that these measures
are in no way a reflection

05:12.844 --> 05:15.289
of the firm's feelings
towards your performance

05:15.724 --> 05:17.404
or your character.

05:18.165 --> 05:19.845
I don't understand.

05:20.724 --> 05:23.932
She's apologizing
for what's about to happen.

05:24.684 --> 05:28.405
Your company e-mail, access to the server,
access to the building,

05:28.484 --> 05:33.165
and your mobile data and phone service
will all be severed as of this meeting.

05:33.644 --> 05:36.972
And this gentleman
will take you to your office

05:37.044 --> 05:39.412
so you can clear out
your personal belongings.

05:43.164 --> 05:47.092
What about what I'm currently working on?
I'm in the middle of something that...

05:47.164 --> 05:51.725
The firm has worked out its transition plan
and is prepared to move forward.

05:51.804 --> 05:54.248
But we do appreciate your concern.

05:54.324 --> 05:58.372
We understand that this is difficult.
And here is my card.

05:59.004 --> 06:00.325
Please contact me in the next few weeks

06:00.326 --> 06:02.724
if you need any assistance
with this transition in your life.

06:08.923 --> 06:09.927
Sir.

06:16.684 --> 06:17.764
Okay.

06:19.203 --> 06:20.327
Okay.

06:22.123 --> 06:23.203
Okay.

06:48.683 --> 06:49.730
Hey.

06:55.163 --> 06:56.603
I'm sorry.

06:58.243 --> 07:00.524
- You still alive?
- For now.

07:01.283 --> 07:02.811
Congratulations.

07:04.083 --> 07:05.802
It was a bloodbath.

07:05.803 --> 07:07.004
I heard.

07:09.443 --> 07:10.883
Listen, Eric,

07:11.603 --> 07:13.805
if there was something I could have done,
I would have done it.

07:13.806 --> 07:14.882
- I know.
- All right?

07:14.883 --> 07:17.283
Yeah, I know. I know.

07:18.042 --> 07:19.166
Okay.

07:19.843 --> 07:20.890
Just tell me,

07:21.643 --> 07:22.723
who was it?

07:23.363 --> 07:25.491
- Come on, Eric.
- Come on, Will.

07:25.563 --> 07:27.211
- Rogers?
- I'm not going to say, you know.

07:27.283 --> 07:28.603
- You know me.
- Robertson?

07:32.483 --> 07:34.562
That cunt. I knew it.

07:34.563 --> 07:36.003
I knew I shouldn't have
fucking gone to her last year.

07:36.083 --> 07:37.925
It wasn't anyone.
Eric, you know what it was?

07:37.926 --> 07:39.243
It was bad luck, and that's all it was.

07:39.244 --> 07:40.290
Yup.

07:40.923 --> 07:41.883
Yup.

07:43.962 --> 07:45.523
All right, well, good luck.

07:45.602 --> 07:46.682
Will?

07:47.483 --> 07:48.771
Come here.

07:51.203 --> 07:53.003
I was just in the middle
of a lot of shit right here

07:53.083 --> 07:54.883
that I think somebody needs
to take a look at.

07:55.682 --> 07:57.123
Eric, listen,

07:58.323 --> 08:00.210
they're telling us
everybody needs to get out of here.

08:00.211 --> 08:02.282
Just leave their stuff.

08:02.283 --> 08:04.803
And while we appreciate your concern,

08:06.563 --> 08:08.886
this is not your problem anymore.

08:13.642 --> 08:14.646
Good luck.

08:19.522 --> 08:20.810
Thank you.

08:28.042 --> 08:30.083
Right this way, Mr. Murphy.

08:49.762 --> 08:51.890
- Eric, I'm very sorry.
- Yeah.

08:52.442 --> 08:55.049
Did they say what was going
to happen with us?

08:55.122 --> 08:57.163
- Jesus, Seth.
- What?

08:57.242 --> 08:59.680
It's going to get pretty ugly
around here for a while.

08:59.681 --> 09:02.409
But, you know, you guys will be all right.

09:03.361 --> 09:05.402
- Good luck, Eric.
- All right.

09:08.002 --> 09:11.406
I'll see you around, okay?
All right. Thank you.

09:31.361 --> 09:32.321
Eric.

09:35.081 --> 09:36.641
I wanted to say thanks.

09:37.482 --> 09:39.282
- It's not necessary.
- Well, it is.

09:39.962 --> 09:42.281
You were the person around here that I...

09:42.316 --> 09:43.569
I know.

09:47.001 --> 09:48.640
Hey, look,

09:48.641 --> 09:51.085
I was working on something,
but they wouldn't let me finish it.

09:51.161 --> 09:53.649
So, take a look at it.

09:55.361 --> 09:56.365
Be careful.

10:16.880 --> 10:17.928
<i>We're sorry.</i>

10:17.929 --> 10:21.849
<i>The telephone you are calling from
is not in service at this time.</i>

10:28.520 --> 10:29.644
Robertson!

10:29.721 --> 10:31.281
Sarah Robertson.

10:31.560 --> 10:32.727
Sarah.

10:34.121 --> 10:35.965
You shut off my phone?

10:36.480 --> 10:38.521
Eric, I didn't do anything.

10:38.801 --> 10:39.848
Fuck you.

11:03.880 --> 11:06.041
Well, that was fucking hideous.

11:06.800 --> 11:09.168
It's gonna get worse before it gets better.

11:09.440 --> 11:10.728
You think?

11:12.160 --> 11:13.207
Much.

11:14.880 --> 11:16.320
You got any Nicorettes?

11:17.440 --> 11:19.284
I'm out of Nicorettes.

11:20.760 --> 11:24.285
Which means in about 10 minutes
I'm going to kill someone.

11:29.279 --> 11:30.403
You all right, Sam?

11:31.560 --> 11:33.120
My dog is dying.

11:37.200 --> 11:38.488
I'm sorry.

11:39.200 --> 11:43.041
Just got off the phone with the vet.
Fucking tumor on her liver.

11:43.800 --> 11:48.088
I was spending, like, $1,000 a day
already just trying to keep her alive.

11:48.160 --> 11:49.240
Yeah,

11:49.840 --> 11:52.884
I don't have a fucking clue
what to do about it.

11:55.919 --> 11:57.883
Well, they're all gone.

11:59.919 --> 12:00.967
So...

12:04.519 --> 12:06.279
How many do we have left?

12:06.280 --> 12:07.524
About 33.

12:07.599 --> 12:11.408
Well, make sure they're all out there.
I've gotta say something.

12:11.480 --> 12:13.540
Yeah, no, they're ready.

12:13.575 --> 12:15.600
They're ready for you.

12:25.360 --> 12:27.280
All right, let's hear it.

12:35.839 --> 12:38.278
You're all still here for a reason.

12:38.279 --> 12:41.519
80% of this floor
was just sent home, forever.

12:42.439 --> 12:44.958
We spent the last hour
saying our goodbyes.

12:44.959 --> 12:47.878
They were good people
and they were good at their jobs,

12:47.879 --> 12:49.122
but you were better.

12:50.079 --> 12:53.118
Now they're gone,
they're not to be thought of again.

12:53.119 --> 12:55.563
This is your opportunity.

12:56.839 --> 12:58.277
On every floor of this building

12:58.278 --> 13:00.198
and in every office,
from Hong Kong to London,

13:00.279 --> 13:01.762
the same thing is happening.

13:01.839 --> 13:03.367
By the time we're done,

13:03.439 --> 13:07.880
three of every seven guys who were
standing between you and your boss' job

13:08.519 --> 13:09.839
are gone.

13:10.719 --> 13:13.446
That is your opportunity.

13:16.438 --> 13:19.123
I've been with this place for 34 years,

13:19.639 --> 13:22.557
and I can tell you this is not the last
time that you're gonna go through this.

13:22.558 --> 13:24.522
But you are all survivors.

13:25.279 --> 13:30.717
And that is how this firm, over 107 years,
has continued to grow stronger.

13:30.718 --> 13:34.200
So keep your heads high. Get back to work.
Let's hear it.

14:24.318 --> 14:26.598
Everyone's going out, man.
You should... Come on.

14:26.599 --> 14:28.605
No, man. I'm cool. Thanks.

14:30.398 --> 14:32.796
Okay. Well, if you change your mind,
just give me a call.

14:32.797 --> 14:34.958
I will.

14:35.038 --> 14:36.118
Come.

14:38.078 --> 14:40.478
- Where you guys going?
- The Grand.

14:41.277 --> 14:43.516
I will call you when I am done.

14:43.517 --> 14:44.838
All right.

14:45.397 --> 14:47.678
Hey, be glad you're still alive.

14:50.038 --> 14:51.118
I am.

15:01.037 --> 15:03.361
- Have a good night, man.
- You, too.

18:00.595 --> 18:01.916
Come on. Come on. Come on.

18:01.995 --> 18:03.043
<i>We're sorry.
You've reached a number...</i>

18:03.115 --> 18:05.439
<i>- Fuck me. Fuck!
- ...that has been disconnected.</i>

18:16.475 --> 18:17.958
- Hello?
- Hey.

18:19.595 --> 18:21.440
<i>- I can't hear you.
- What?</i>

18:21.915 --> 18:23.520
Can you go outside? It's too loud.

18:23.595 --> 18:26.879
Hold on a second. It's loud.
Just give me a second.

18:30.395 --> 18:31.835
<i>- All right, what's up?
- Hey, where are you?</i>

18:32.035 --> 18:34.643
<i>- Lugo.
- Okay. Are you with Will?</i>

18:34.714 --> 18:36.482
<i>- Yeah. Will Emerson?
- Yeah.</i>

18:36.555 --> 18:38.399
Yeah. I think he's still here. Why?

18:39.794 --> 18:43.199
All right. I need you to get Will,
and I need you guys to come back up here.

18:43.275 --> 18:44.955
<i>- Where?
- To the office.</i>

18:45.035 --> 18:46.595
<i>- What?
- I'm serious.</i>

18:47.754 --> 18:50.873
Wait a sec... You want me
to get our boss' boss out of a club

18:50.874 --> 18:53.198
and bring him back to the office
at 10:00 on a Thursday night?

18:53.514 --> 18:55.915
Well, our boss got axed,
so technically he is our boss,

18:55.994 --> 18:58.918
<i>- and yes, that is what I want you to do.
- Why?</i>

18:59.355 --> 19:01.843
Look, man. Just trust me, okay?
I need you guys back here now.

19:01.914 --> 19:04.118
<i>All right. We'll be there in 10.</i>

19:06.114 --> 19:07.194
Fuck.

19:23.034 --> 19:25.958
Have I ever told you
how much I love your bag?

19:26.034 --> 19:27.081
No, really.

19:27.154 --> 19:30.078
- Do you have a little dress that matches it?
- Yeah, I do.

19:30.154 --> 19:33.593
Because you could bounce around in it
like a fucking girl.

19:33.594 --> 19:34.641
Hey!

19:35.194 --> 19:37.758
Look who's burning the candle
at both ends.

19:37.834 --> 19:40.033
Why didn't you come out with us?

19:40.034 --> 19:43.353
There's no more cuts planned.
You don't have to kiss my arse.

19:43.354 --> 19:45.436
I frankly don't even know
what it is you guys do.

19:45.437 --> 19:47.518
Well, I'm really sorry
I had to bring you guys back here,

19:47.519 --> 19:49.358
- but...
- That's all right.

19:49.433 --> 19:51.757
- What's going on?
- Look at this.

19:51.834 --> 19:54.753
- Eric gave me this file before he left.
- Eric...

19:54.754 --> 19:57.122
Dale. And he told me
that he couldn't quite figure it out.

19:57.123 --> 19:58.958
And the last thing he said to me

19:59.033 --> 20:01.478
before the elevator doors closed was,
"Be careful".

20:02.394 --> 20:04.792
- He said, "Be careful"?
- Yeah. So, obviously, I'm a little curious.

20:04.793 --> 20:05.960
I start to get into it a little bit,

20:06.033 --> 20:08.237
and I realize that the only thing
that he's missing...

20:08.314 --> 20:11.402
- This is not good, Will.
- All right. Okay. So what is he doing here?

20:12.434 --> 20:14.562
No, no. Go to model four.
It makes more sense.

20:14.634 --> 20:16.312
Okay. All right.

20:16.313 --> 20:17.754
What is this?

20:18.273 --> 20:21.481
This is basically everything that
we have in our books at any given time.

20:21.553 --> 20:24.041
But, what Eric was trying to do
was to work these numbers

20:24.114 --> 20:27.354
for levels of volatility that fall
outside of the standard VAR model.

20:27.433 --> 20:29.912
- What are those levels?
- It's fairly complicated.

20:29.913 --> 20:30.993
Simplify.

20:31.514 --> 20:34.918
The volatility levels are set
using historic patterns, basically,

20:34.993 --> 20:37.315
and then stretching those patterns
out another 10, 15% roughly.

20:37.316 --> 20:38.273
All right, so?

20:38.353 --> 20:41.922
So, we are starting
to test those historic patterns.

20:43.073 --> 20:44.120
When?

20:44.513 --> 20:46.072
- Today.
- Tuesday.

20:46.073 --> 20:49.041
Monday. Last Friday and Wednesday.

20:49.113 --> 20:50.880
Two Fridays ago.

20:51.153 --> 20:52.833
All right. I get it.

20:54.873 --> 20:56.152
Fuck me.

20:56.153 --> 20:59.192
Once this thing gets going
in the wrong direction,

20:59.193 --> 21:00.672
this is fucking huge.

21:00.673 --> 21:01.994
How huge?

21:03.513 --> 21:05.641
Well, the losses are greater than
the current value of the company.

21:05.713 --> 21:08.277
Projected losses.
The projected losses, Will.

21:08.832 --> 21:11.200
- And this is just our floor?
- Yes.

21:13.833 --> 21:14.880
Where the fuck is Eric Dale?

21:14.953 --> 21:16.513
I don't know. I tried to call him.
His phone is off.

21:16.593 --> 21:17.595
What do you mean?

21:17.596 --> 21:19.874
They turned everybody's phone off
that they axed today.

21:19.875 --> 21:21.193
Fucking ruthless.

21:21.872 --> 21:25.157
- Did you try his personal cell?
- Yeah, I called his cell phone. it's not on.

21:25.233 --> 21:27.556
- Call his home.
- At this hour?

21:27.632 --> 21:29.836
Yeah. Do we even know if he's right?

21:29.913 --> 21:32.761
- Looks pretty fucking right to me.
- It does.

21:35.513 --> 21:37.631
Mrs. Dale, it's Will Emerson.

21:37.632 --> 21:40.436
I'm fine, thank you. May I speak with Eric?

21:42.793 --> 21:44.953
No, we've tried that.
His phone appears to be off.

21:44.954 --> 21:48.717
Listen, could you have him call me
the moment he comes in?

21:48.792 --> 21:51.193
The moment he walks through the door.

21:51.272 --> 21:52.991
Thank you so much.

21:52.992 --> 21:54.312
Goodbye.

21:54.392 --> 21:55.396
Where the fuck is he?

21:55.472 --> 21:57.120
- Doesn't he have, like, three kids?
- So?

21:57.155 --> 21:59.676
Fuck, I don't know, would you go home?

22:01.312 --> 22:02.993
I know where he is.

22:04.112 --> 22:05.595
I need you two to go and get him.

22:05.672 --> 22:07.516
There will be a car
waiting for you downstairs.

22:07.592 --> 22:09.272
- You need to go.
- Right now?

22:09.352 --> 22:10.956
Yeah, right now.

22:11.032 --> 22:12.320
What are you going to do?

22:12.321 --> 22:14.113
I'm going to call Sam.

22:18.112 --> 22:19.432
Fuck me.

22:35.111 --> 22:36.836
<i>- Yes?
- It's Will.</i>

22:37.592 --> 22:39.476
It's 11:00 at night.

22:39.511 --> 22:41.431
I know. I'm sorry. I wouldn't have called.

22:42.352 --> 22:43.880
What's the problem?

22:44.632 --> 22:46.399
I think you need to get back here.

22:47.031 --> 22:48.232
What?

22:48.831 --> 22:50.239
<i>Sam, listen...</i>

22:50.312 --> 22:51.990
it's 11:00 at night.

22:51.991 --> 22:56.159
I'm well aware of the fucking time, Sam.
I'm telling you, you need to see this.

22:56.231 --> 22:57.311
<i>See what?</i>

22:57.672 --> 22:58.676
It's...

22:59.271 --> 23:00.679
E- mail it to me.

23:01.112 --> 23:04.080
I don't think that, that
would be a good idea.

23:06.951 --> 23:08.512
I'm on my way.

23:14.032 --> 23:15.636
Look at these people.

23:17.592 --> 23:21.716
Wandering around with absolutely no idea
what's about to happen.

23:25.111 --> 23:26.116
Right?

23:26.951 --> 23:29.919
Well, I try to not let
work get to me like that.

23:30.632 --> 23:32.672
I've noticed that about you.

23:34.192 --> 23:36.515
Come on. We're 23 years old.

23:37.471 --> 23:39.230
- I'm 28.
- All right, 28.

23:39.231 --> 23:40.475
Whatever, it's the same thing,

23:40.551 --> 23:45.352
but I made nearly a quarter
of a million dollars last year.

23:46.631 --> 23:47.678
Fuck. For what?

23:48.311 --> 23:50.559
I push numbers around
on a computer screen.

23:50.911 --> 23:53.519
A bunch of glorified crack addicts
are willing to take that information,

23:53.591 --> 23:54.551
and they pretend to understand it,

23:54.631 --> 23:56.670
and they bet it against some other jock
halfway around the world

23:56.671 --> 23:57.992
who, you know, if he wasn't doing this,

23:58.070 --> 24:01.278
he'd be in an OTB somewhere,
putting it all on number seven, you know?

24:02.271 --> 24:05.392
At the end of the day,
one guy wins, one guy loses.

24:06.831 --> 24:09.832
You do know it's a little more
complicated than that, right?

24:10.231 --> 24:11.311
Yeah.

24:17.950 --> 24:20.510
It's Will. He wants to know if we found him.
What do I say?

24:20.511 --> 24:22.998
Let's say that we haven't found him yet.

24:23.710 --> 24:24.757
Okay.

24:47.190 --> 24:48.510
- Hey.
- Hey.

24:48.511 --> 24:49.590
So?

24:50.870 --> 24:51.874
Eric Dale.

24:51.951 --> 24:53.239
Oh, Jesus.

24:54.070 --> 24:56.558
Before he leaves the building,
escorted by fucking security, by the way...

24:56.630 --> 24:58.070
- I had nothing to do with that.
- I know.

24:58.150 --> 24:59.230
I'm sorry. Go on.

24:59.310 --> 25:01.918
Before he leaves the building,
he hands this disk to Peter Sullivan.

25:01.990 --> 25:03.396
- Who's Peter Sullivan again?
- Doesn't matter.

25:03.397 --> 25:04.994
- He's one of Eric's guys.
- All right.

25:04.995 --> 25:10.555
But before the elevator doors are closing,
the last thing that he says is, "Be careful".

25:11.709 --> 25:13.314
"Be careful"?

25:13.390 --> 25:14.394
Yeah.

25:14.470 --> 25:15.517
- "Be careful"?
- Yeah.

25:15.590 --> 25:17.270
- Why?
- Take a look.

25:20.190 --> 25:22.231
Oh, Jesus. You Know
I can't fucking read these things.

25:22.232 --> 25:23.670
Just speak to me in English.

25:23.671 --> 25:27.674
All right. Basically, this Kid, Peter Sullivan,
he gets all inspired by your pep talk.

25:27.750 --> 25:29.469
Nice job, by the way.

25:29.470 --> 25:32.148
And he delves straight in after work.

25:32.149 --> 25:33.350
And I think he nailed it.

