and Management Office at MBS.

45:05.575 --> 45:09.177
Please. Just relax. Stand up.
Tell us in a clear voice.

45:09.255 --> 45:11.536
What is the nature of the problem?

45:13.576 --> 45:14.623
Okay.

45:16.295 --> 45:19.654
As you probably know,
over the last 36 to 40 months

45:19.655 --> 45:22.743
the firm has begun packaging

45:22.815 --> 45:27.736
new MBS products that
combine several different tranches

45:27.815 --> 45:30.936
of rating classifications
in one tradable security.

45:31.815 --> 45:33.895
This has been enormously profitable,

45:33.896 --> 45:36.024
as I imagine you noticed.

45:36.096 --> 45:37.263
I have.

45:37.455 --> 45:39.584
The firm is currently doing
a considerable amount

45:39.655 --> 45:40.660
of this business every day.

45:40.735 --> 45:44.494
Now the problem, which is, I guess,
why we are here tonight,

45:44.495 --> 45:47.496
is that is takes us, the
firm, about a month

45:48.015 --> 45:52.174
to layer these products correctly,
thereby posing a challenge

45:52.175 --> 45:54.378
from a Risk Management standpoint.

45:54.615 --> 45:56.383
And, Mr. Sullivan, that challenge is?

45:56.775 --> 46:00.814
We have to hold these assets on our books
longer than we might ideally like to.

46:00.815 --> 46:01.982
Yes.

46:02.055 --> 46:04.782
But the key factor here is
these are essentially just mortgages.

46:04.855 --> 46:08.613
So that has allowed us to push
the leverage considerably beyond

46:08.614 --> 46:12.139
what you might be willing or allowed to do
in any other circumstance,

46:12.215 --> 46:16.023
thereby pushing the risk profile
without raising any red flags.

46:17.694 --> 46:19.419
Now... Thank you, Mr. Sullivan. Sit down.

46:19.495 --> 46:21.818
What I'm guessing your report here says,

46:21.895 --> 46:24.219
and give me some rope here.

46:24.294 --> 46:28.135
What I'm guessing it says is that
considering the, shall we say,

46:28.215 --> 46:31.259
bumpy road we've been on
the last week or so,

46:31.335 --> 46:35.974
that the figures your brilliant co-workers
up the line ahead of you have come up with

46:36.009 --> 46:38.253
don't make much sense any more

46:38.254 --> 46:40.655
considering what's taking place today.

46:40.734 --> 46:42.414
Actually, not what's taking place today,

46:42.415 --> 46:45.142
but what's already taken place
over the last two weeks.

46:45.215 --> 46:48.455
So, you're saying
this has already happened?

46:48.534 --> 46:49.854
Sort of.

46:51.255 --> 46:52.455
Sort of.

46:53.614 --> 46:58.142
And, Mr. Sullivan, what does your model
say that, that means for us here.

46:59.294 --> 47:01.782
Well, that's where it becomes a projection.

47:02.014 --> 47:03.181
But...

47:05.414 --> 47:07.978
You're speaking with me, Mr. Sullivan.

47:08.374 --> 47:09.738
Well, sir,

47:10.374 --> 47:14.093
if those assets decrease by just 25%

47:14.094 --> 47:15.981
and remain on our books,

47:16.574 --> 47:20.622
that loss would be greater than
the current market capitalization

47:20.694 --> 47:22.538
of this entire company.

47:25.894 --> 47:28.742
So, what you're telling me

47:30.254 --> 47:33.374
is that the music is about to stop

47:34.613 --> 47:37.657
and we're going to be left
holding the biggest bag

47:37.734 --> 47:39.022
of odorous excrement

47:39.293 --> 47:41.901
ever assembled in the history of

47:43.693 --> 47:45.057
capitalism.

47:48.934 --> 47:53.014
Sir, I'm not sure that I would put
it that way. But let me clarify.

47:53.533 --> 47:55.653
Using your analogy,

47:55.654 --> 47:57.454
what this model shows

47:58.493 --> 48:01.221
is the music, so to speak, just slowing.

48:02.534 --> 48:04.812
If the music were to stop, as you put it,

48:04.813 --> 48:07.978
then this model wouldn't be even close
to that scenario.

48:08.054 --> 48:10.661
It would be considerably worse.

48:14.533 --> 48:17.141
Let me tell you something, Mr. Sullivan.

48:18.133 --> 48:22.542
Do you care to know why
I'm in this chair with you all?

48:22.613 --> 48:24.937
I mean, why I earn the big bucks?

48:26.213 --> 48:27.173
Yes.

48:27.254 --> 48:30.374
I'm here for one reason
and one reason alone.

48:30.853 --> 48:36.701
I'm here to guess what the music might do
a week, a month, a year from now.

48:37.973 --> 48:39.261
That's it.

48:40.093 --> 48:41.217
Nothing more.

48:43.493 --> 48:45.577
And standing here tonight,

48:46.373 --> 48:51.741
I'm afraid that I don't hear a thing.

48:54.333 --> 48:55.500
Just

48:57.852 --> 48:59.336
silence.

49:14.492 --> 49:18.497
So, now that we Know the music has
stopped, what can we do about it?

49:19.252 --> 49:21.413
Mr. Cohen? Ms. Robertson?

49:22.773 --> 49:26.254
I'm afraid I think this is where
you're supposed to step back in.

49:26.692 --> 49:30.053
Lord knows we've relied enough
on Mr. Sullivan tonight.

49:31.652 --> 49:33.661
What do you have for us?

49:41.293 --> 49:45.297
What have I told you since
the first day you stepped into my office?

49:46.172 --> 49:48.976
There are three ways to make a living
in this business,

49:49.052 --> 49:52.293
be first, be smarter, or cheat.

49:53.172 --> 49:54.852
Now, I don't cheat.

49:55.332 --> 49:59.576
And although I like to think we have
some pretty smart people in this building,

50:00.172 --> 50:03.577
it sure is a hell of a lot
easier to just be first.

50:04.332 --> 50:06.057
Sell it all. Today.

50:08.772 --> 50:10.780
Is that even possible, Sam?

50:11.252 --> 50:13.096
Yes, but at what cost?

50:14.812 --> 50:16.372
I'll have to pay.

50:18.052 --> 50:19.491
Really?

50:19.492 --> 50:20.855
I think so.

50:22.012 --> 50:24.260
Where is this going to come back to us?

50:25.012 --> 50:26.059
Everywhere.

50:26.851 --> 50:31.260
Sam, I don't think you seem to understand
what your boy here has just said.

50:34.851 --> 50:36.456
If I made you,

50:37.212 --> 50:38.859
how would you do this?

50:44.492 --> 50:47.580
You call the traders in for their normal
6:30 meeting and you be honest with them.

50:47.652 --> 50:50.052
Because they're going to know
it's the end either way.

50:50.252 --> 50:53.132
You're going to have to throw them a bone,
and a pretty big one.

50:53.211 --> 50:55.535
And then you've got to
come out of the gates storming.

50:55.612 --> 50:57.772
No swaps. No nothing.

50:57.851 --> 51:00.055
40% done by 10:15. By 11:00,

51:00.131 --> 51:01.570
all your trades have to be gone

51:01.571 --> 51:03.895
because by lunchtime,
word's going to be out.

51:04.851 --> 51:08.810
And by 2:00 you're going to be selling
at 65 cents on the dollar, if you're lucky.

51:08.811 --> 51:11.692
And then the feds are going to be in here,
up your ass, trying to slow you down.

51:11.771 --> 51:12.938
Ramesh?

51:13.011 --> 51:15.530
They can slow you down.
They can't stop you.

51:15.531 --> 51:16.810
It's yours to sell.

51:16.811 --> 51:18.895
But, John, even if

51:19.811 --> 51:22.931
we manage to pull that off,
and that's saying something,

51:24.451 --> 51:27.331
the real question is,
who are we selling this to?

51:27.811 --> 51:30.299
Same people we've been selling it to
the last two years,

51:30.371 --> 51:31.970
and whoever else will buy it.

51:31.971 --> 51:34.219
But, John, if you do this,

51:35.570 --> 51:38.419
you will kill the market for years.
It's over.

51:40.571 --> 51:43.375
And you're selling something
that you know has no value.

51:43.810 --> 51:48.098
We are selling to willing buyers
of the current fair market price.

51:48.771 --> 51:52.130
So that we may survive.

51:52.131 --> 51:55.819
You will never sell anything
to any of those people ever again.

51:55.890 --> 51:57.134
I understand.

51:57.250 --> 51:58.975
- Do you?
- Do you?

52:00.171 --> 52:01.730
This is it!

52:01.731 --> 52:03.935
I'm telling you. This is it.

52:14.850 --> 52:16.171
Now, it's 4:00.

52:16.770 --> 52:19.775
Jared, you've got till 5:00 to
break this down and draw me up a plan.

52:19.810 --> 52:23.935
Is there anybody else who knows what's
in here at the moment, block by block?

52:24.610 --> 52:25.898
Eric Dale.

52:26.450 --> 52:27.574
And where is he?

52:27.970 --> 52:30.610
As of today, he's no longer with the firm.

52:30.930 --> 52:33.298
We have been trying to locate him.

52:37.050 --> 52:38.054
- Carmelo.
- Yes.

52:38.130 --> 52:40.138
Get me Eric Dale here by 6:30.

52:40.610 --> 52:41.811
It's done.

52:42.090 --> 52:44.010
We meet back here in an hour.

52:46.370 --> 52:48.050
Sam, let's talk.

53:00.770 --> 53:02.734
This is a hell of a town.

53:04.490 --> 53:07.371
I've always loved this place,
since the day I arrived.

53:07.449 --> 53:08.770
Everything about it.

53:17.290 --> 53:19.974
Sam, are you going to go with me on this?

53:21.770 --> 53:23.494
I don't know, John.

53:25.210 --> 53:27.010
This one is very ugly.

53:28.609 --> 53:30.573
You and I, we're salesmen.

53:31.329 --> 53:33.889
We sell. That's what we do.
It's not complicated.

53:33.890 --> 53:35.134
Exactly.

53:35.930 --> 53:38.417
And you know damn well
you don't sell anything to anybody

53:38.489 --> 53:40.333
unless you think they're gonna
come back for more.

53:40.409 --> 53:43.530
That's the lesson we learned.
And tomorrow, we're done.

53:44.050 --> 53:45.130
But this is it, Sam.

53:45.209 --> 53:47.337
You keep saying that.
What's that supposed to mean?

53:47.649 --> 53:49.329
This is the big one.

53:49.969 --> 53:52.653
Most of us aren't going to
make it out of this one.

53:52.729 --> 53:54.693
- Us?
- The Street.

53:55.649 --> 53:57.057
What are you talking about?

53:57.409 --> 53:59.973
This isn't the last situation
I'm gonna have to deal with this week.

54:00.049 --> 54:01.216
This is just the start.

54:01.729 --> 54:03.497
It's the start 'cause you're starting it.

54:03.809 --> 54:06.733
Maybe. But I don't believe that.
Not this time.

54:07.489 --> 54:09.617
The numbers,
they just don't add up any more.

54:09.689 --> 54:13.127
I agree with you there.
I've been saying that for years.

54:13.128 --> 54:16.293
If this kid out there can
come up with this, then...

54:17.248 --> 54:19.889
Look, I just don't think I can
walk in there knowing what I know

54:19.969 --> 54:21.574
and put the hammer down on these guys.

54:22.529 --> 54:24.613
When did you start getting so soft, Sam?

54:25.129 --> 54:27.856
Fuck you, soft. You're panicking

54:30.529 --> 54:34.774
If you're the first out of the door,
that's not called panicking.

54:40.448 --> 54:44.137
You're obviously operating
with more information than I have.

54:45.889 --> 54:48.496
But I think this will destroy this firm.

54:48.968 --> 54:50.528
No one will ever trust you again.

54:50.529 --> 54:53.256
You're knowingly putting people
out of business, full stop.

54:55.808 --> 54:58.012
You let me deal with that, Sam.

55:12.448 --> 55:13.495
How'd it go?

55:14.488 --> 55:16.529
This is a fucking shit show.

55:17.328 --> 55:19.772
- They're gonna go with it?
- Probably.

55:20.608 --> 55:21.732
Jesus.

55:23.408 --> 55:25.252
Remember this day, boys.

55:27.328 --> 55:28.932
Remember this day.

55:43.968 --> 55:46.052
So, what's the strategy here?

55:46.127 --> 55:47.328
That's where I'm headed right now.

55:47.408 --> 55:49.175
Downstairs to work on it with my guys.

55:49.248 --> 55:51.649
No, no. You and I with John.

55:57.168 --> 56:01.447
I'm not sure that we need one, Sarah.
That's not the way I do things.

56:01.448 --> 56:02.649
Please.

56:04.767 --> 56:07.528
Listen, he knows where we've stood on this

56:07.608 --> 56:08.928
all along.

56:09.567 --> 56:11.454
That's exactly my point.

56:11.968 --> 56:15.536
And knowing what was discussed
by both you and I,

56:16.007 --> 56:19.007
I don't see how this could
provide you with anything

56:19.008 --> 56:21.648
other than a false sense of comfort.

56:21.728 --> 56:24.848
I'm not looking for
a sense of comfort here, Sarah.

56:25.887 --> 56:28.451
I don't think there's one to be found.

56:38.527 --> 56:40.491
So, again, what's the strategy here?

56:42.887 --> 56:45.287
I'm just not sure
there's much more to do on this.

56:46.287 --> 56:47.892
It's very simple.

56:48.407 --> 56:51.168
Don't even think about fucking me on this.

56:52.167 --> 56:54.208
'Cause if we're going down,

56:55.287 --> 56:57.371
then you damn well know it'll be together.

56:58.927 --> 56:59.975
No.

57:00.767 --> 57:02.611
I'm not sure that I do know that.

57:23.847 --> 57:24.927
Hey.

57:25.566 --> 57:27.007
Oh, I'm sorry.

57:40.086 --> 57:42.847
What do you guys think
Tuld made last year?

57:44.847 --> 57:46.451
Would you shut the fuck up?

57:46.526 --> 57:47.934
86 million.

57:49.126 --> 57:51.046
In bonuses and salary.

57:51.966 --> 57:53.767
- Really?
- Sure, it's public record.

57:53.846 --> 57:56.050
That is a lot of fucking money.

57:57.207 --> 57:58.854
He was worth a billion.

57:58.926 --> 57:59.886
Was?

58:01.086 --> 58:02.374
Till today.

58:03.166 --> 58:04.367
Really?

58:05.886 --> 58:07.206
You'll see.

58:10.046 --> 58:12.774
I'm going to get some coffee.
You guys want anything else?

58:12.846 --> 58:15.574
- I'm all right.
- I could use some real air.

58:15.646 --> 58:17.566
- Probably a good idea.
- Is it all right, Will?

58:17.646 --> 58:19.534
- Is what all right?
- If I get out of here for a minute?

58:19.535 --> 58:21.245
Of course, it's not a prison.

58:21.246 --> 58:23.406
You want me to hold your hand?

58:27.846 --> 58:30.410
Why did they put all this fruit on it?

58:39.406 --> 58:41.404
Hello, Will Emerson.

58:41.405 --> 58:42.529
Hello.

58:46.006 --> 58:47.207
Right.

58:48.486 --> 58:50.766
No, thank you. I understand.

58:53.246 --> 58:55.133
No, we'll be discreet.

58:56.605 --> 58:57.893
Thank you.

58:58.525 --> 59:00.173
- What?
- Eric's wife.

59:00.686 --> 59:02.725
He's alive, he's home,
he doesn't want to speak to us,

59:02.726 --> 59:04.133
and he doesn't know that she rang me.

59:04.205 --> 59:05.810
- Where's he live?
- Heights.

59:06.205 --> 59:07.809
- Shall I call Tuld's guy?
- No.

59:08.285 --> 59:10.533
It's Eric. The last thing we need
is those guys going over there.

59:10.605 --> 59:12.011
No, you two go get him
and try to bring him here.

59:12.012 --> 59:14.373
- But you got to be back by 6:00 a.m.
- All right.

59:17.525 --> 59:19.130
I hate Brooklyn.

59:24.005 --> 59:25.010
May I come in?

59:25.085 --> 59:27.169
Of course. Please, sit down.

59:32.805 --> 59:33.809
So...

59:37.805 --> 59:39.933
We're going to do this thing.

59:42.925 --> 59:44.049
Okay.

59:45.284 --> 59:47.204
It's going to be tight.

59:48.925 --> 59:50.409
Is Sam on board?

59:50.765 --> 59:52.009
Not yet.

59:55.645 --> 59:56.933
Sarah,

59:57.525 --> 01:00:01.365
I need a head to feed to the traders
on the floor and the board.

01:00:05.884 --> 01:00:07.803
Is it me or Cohen?

01:00:07.804 --> 01:00:09.092
It's you.

01:00:18.364 --> 01:00:22.128
Of course, you're well aware
that I filtered several warnings

01:00:22.204 --> 01:00:24.769
to you and Cohen about this a year ago.

01:00:25.204 --> 01:00:29.449
I really don't think that's the best path
for you to take at this point.

01:00:33.324 --> 01:00:36.128
You're going to be well taken care of here.

01:00:38.724 --> 01:00:40.449
Obviously, it is

01:00:41.444 --> 01:00:42.404
quite complicated.

01:00:42.484 --> 01:00:44.525
John, I was told under
no uncertain terms...

01:00:44.604 --> 01:00:46.723
It was always a very gray area.

01:00:46.724 --> 01:00:51.612
Actually, it was made very clear
at the time by you, me, and Cohen.

01:00:53.444 --> 01:00:56.891
I'd really appreciate it
if you didn't fight me on this.

01:01:08.564 --> 01:01:11.084
We all fucked this one up pretty good.

01:01:11.884 --> 01:01:13.008
Yes.

01:01:15.284 --> 01:01:17.283
We need you to stay here
until this is finished

01:01:17.284 --> 01:01:19.522
and the market's closed.

01:01:19.523 --> 01:01:20.931
I understand.

01:01:23.164 --> 01:01:26.568
They'll go over the numbers
with you downstairs.

01:01:26.643 --> 01:01:27.931
Good luck.

01:01:44.883 --> 01:01:46.803
Oh, fuck. Jared's coming.

01:01:48.004 --> 01:01:50.045
What's the boy wonder want?

01:01:55.643 --> 01:01:57.967
- You got a minute?
- Just off to pick up Eric.

01:01:58.043 --> 01:01:59.723
Yeah. I know. It will only take a second.

01:01:59.804 --> 01:02:01.092
All right, what is it?

01:02:01.403 --> 01:02:03.684
Tuld and I have concerns that Sam

01:02:03.763 --> 01:02:06.612
may not be willing to step up
and do the right thing here.

01:02:07.003 --> 01:02:08.367
This has never been a problem.

01:02:08.444 --> 01:02:09.448
No, it hasn't.

01:02:09.643 --> 01:02:12.808
But sometimes,
in acute situations such as this,

01:02:12.883 --> 01:02:18.044
often what is right can take on
multiple interpretations.

01:02:21.883 --> 01:02:23.324
Sam will step up.

01:02:23.403 --> 01:02:26.044
Oh, I know he will. But if he doesn't...

01:02:27.522 --> 01:02:30.566
But if he doesn't,
we need to know that you will.

01:02:32.643 --> 01:02:33.603
Thank you.

01:02:33.683 --> 01:02:36.007
You need to know that I will what?

01:02:36.083 --> 01:02:37.763
That you'll step up.

01:02:39.363 --> 01:02:42.124
I have no doubt that
Sam will make the right decision.

01:02:42.202 --> 01:02:43.841
But just to make it clear,

01:02:43.842 --> 01:02:46.450
he and I have always had
the same interpretation of what's right,

01:02:48.443 --> 01:02:50.843
no matter how acute the situation.

01:05:30.200 --> 01:05:31.839
Jesus, that's a nice place.

01:05:31.840 --> 01:05:34.044
Yeah, it is. He just bought it.

01:05:35.601 --> 01:05:37.281
I hope it was with cash.

01:05:38.361 --> 01:05:40.925
Fuck me,
you're a heartless little shit sometimes.

01:05:42.680 --> 01:05:44.121
And it wasn't.

01:05:45.880 --> 01:05:48.128
Don't touch any of the buttons.

01:05:54.281 --> 01:05:56.441
- What are you doing here?
- Hey.

01:06:03.000 --> 01:06:06.044
So, Peter finished the model
you were working on.

01:06:06.680 --> 01:06:07.804
Really?

01:06:08.240 --> 01:06:09.681
It caused a shit storm.

01:06:10.160 --> 01:06:11.568
I bet it did.

01:06:12.600 --> 01:06:13.888
You think he's right?

01:06:14.640 --> 01:06:16.244
I know he's right.

01:06:18.400 --> 01:06:19.447
Fuck.

01:06:21.400 --> 01:06:22.688
All right.

01:06:27.640 --> 01:06:29.888
So Jared Cohen called
an emergency meeting

01:06:29.960 --> 01:06:31.521
with the senior partners last night.

01:06:31.800 --> 01:06:34.080
And based on your findings,

01:06:34.160 --> 01:06:37.248
they've decided to liquidate
our entire position.

01:06:37.800 --> 01:06:38.760
Today.

01:06:41.160 --> 01:06:43.124
I'm very sorry about that.

01:06:49.320 --> 01:06:52.364
They're worried about you being out here
and they want me to bring you back.

01:06:53.039 --> 01:06:54.206
Please.

01:06:54.760 --> 01:06:56.478
I'm just saying.

01:06:56.479 --> 01:06:58.039
- Fuck them. Fuck them.
- Eric...

01:06:58.040 --> 01:07:00.604
- Don't be rash.
- Forget it. I signed my paper. I'm out.

01:07:00.680 --> 01:07:03.080
- They'll pay you.
- They got nothing on me.

01:07:03.160 --> 01:07:04.207
They'll pay you.

01:07:05.040 --> 01:07:07.168
I've been paid enough already.

01:07:11.080 --> 01:07:12.159
Fuck.

01:07:15.319 --> 01:07:17.687
Do you know I built a bridge once?

01:07:18.439 --> 01:07:20.087
- Sorry?
- A bridge.

01:07:21.240 --> 01:07:22.920
No, I didn't know that.

01:07:22.999 --> 01:07:25.127
I was an engineer by trade.

01:07:27.280 --> 01:07:31.164
It went from Dilles Bottom, Ohio,
to Moundsville, West Virginia.

